WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.365 align:middle line:90%


00:00:04.365 --> 00:00:07.760 align:middle line:90%
[AUDIO LOGO]

00:00:07.760 --> 00:00:10.993 align:middle line:90%


00:00:10.993 --> 00:00:12.910 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE NOORY: Would
you be able to ascertain

00:00:12.910 --> 00:00:15.790 align:middle line:84%
their personality,
their character

00:00:15.790 --> 00:00:17.168 align:middle line:90%
from just reading a palm?

00:00:17.168 --> 00:00:18.460 align:middle line:90%
>>VERNON MAHABAL: Yes, you can.

00:00:18.460 --> 00:00:22.060 align:middle line:84%
Our activities determine
how the palm looks.

00:00:22.060 --> 00:00:24.790 align:middle line:84%
Lines-- lines can
change, and that

00:00:24.790 --> 00:00:27.490 align:middle line:84%
means that we're either
doing our destiny

00:00:27.490 --> 00:00:28.780 align:middle line:90%
or not doing our destiny.

00:00:28.780 --> 00:00:32.259 align:middle line:84%
Life doesn't come with
instructions, but it does.

00:00:32.259 --> 00:00:33.638 align:middle line:90%
It's on our hands.

00:00:33.638 --> 00:00:34.805 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's fascinating.

00:00:34.805 --> 00:00:35.605 align:middle line:90%
>>MAHABAL: Yeah.

00:00:35.605 --> 00:00:36.670 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It truly is.

00:00:36.670 --> 00:00:40.860 align:middle line:90%


00:00:40.860 --> 00:00:43.140 align:middle line:84%
Well, welcome to this
edition of "Beyond Belief."

00:00:43.140 --> 00:00:45.570 align:middle line:10%
Vernon Mahabal is
with us, a palmist

00:00:45.570 --> 00:00:48.360 align:middle line:10%
and the founder and
director of the Palmistry

00:00:48.360 --> 00:00:50.290 align:middle line:10%
Institute in California.

00:00:50.290 --> 00:00:54.090 align:middle line:84%
He has read literally
thousands of hands

00:00:54.090 --> 00:00:56.730 align:middle line:84%
and given hundreds of
lectures on the ancient art

00:00:56.730 --> 00:00:57.600 align:middle line:90%
of palmistry.

00:00:57.600 --> 00:00:59.302 align:middle line:84%
Vernon, welcome to
"Beyond Belief."

00:00:59.302 --> 00:01:00.510 align:middle line:90%
>>MAHABAL: Thank you, George.

00:01:00.510 --> 00:01:02.768 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: How did you get
involved in reading palms?

00:01:02.768 --> 00:01:04.560 align:middle line:84%
This isn't something
that somebody wakes up

00:01:04.560 --> 00:01:06.232 align:middle line:84%
in the morning and
says, this is what

00:01:06.232 --> 00:01:07.440 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to do for a living.

00:01:07.440 --> 00:01:09.360 align:middle line:90%
What happened?

00:01:09.360 --> 00:01:12.240 align:middle line:10%
>>MAHABAL: I was
always drawn to it.

00:01:12.240 --> 00:01:15.630 align:middle line:84%
Even when I was in high
school, I was reading hands.

00:01:15.630 --> 00:01:20.642 align:middle line:84%
I actually got a book on
palmistry in my school library.

00:01:20.642 --> 00:01:23.100 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I bet you were the
head of the party, weren't you?

00:01:23.100 --> 00:01:24.308 align:middle line:90%
>>MAHABAL: Not at that point.

00:01:24.308 --> 00:01:25.740 align:middle line:90%
My friends thought I was crazy.

00:01:25.740 --> 00:01:27.210 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Really?

00:01:27.210 --> 00:01:28.852 align:middle line:84%
>>MAHABAL: I would
take people's--

00:01:28.852 --> 00:01:30.810 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, what did
you see about the palms

00:01:30.810 --> 00:01:32.710 align:middle line:84%
that you liked in
order to do it?

00:01:32.710 --> 00:01:35.460 align:middle line:90%
What was your curiosity factor?

00:01:35.460 --> 00:01:40.530 align:middle line:10%
>>MAHABAL: My curiosity
factor was that I just

00:01:40.530 --> 00:01:47.090 align:middle line:10%
felt intuitively that there
was something about hands that

00:01:47.090 --> 00:01:49.160 align:middle line:10%
told about the human mechanism.

00:01:49.160 --> 00:01:54.440 align:middle line:84%
And even when I was a kid, when
I was, let's say, 10 or 11,

00:01:54.440 --> 00:01:57.470 align:middle line:84%
I would stare at my hands
and just ask myself,

00:01:57.470 --> 00:01:58.550 align:middle line:90%
what are all these lines?

00:01:58.550 --> 00:02:00.680 align:middle line:84%
What are there are
these configurations?

00:02:00.680 --> 00:02:02.930 align:middle line:90%
What do they mean?

00:02:02.930 --> 00:02:05.630 align:middle line:84%
So I was, I think, intuitively
drawn to it from, maybe,

00:02:05.630 --> 00:02:07.100 align:middle line:90%
a previous life or something.

00:02:07.100 --> 00:02:09.169 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Is every
hand different?

00:02:09.169 --> 00:02:10.910 align:middle line:84%
>>MAHABAL: Every
palm is different.

00:02:10.910 --> 00:02:13.340 align:middle line:84%
Even your left--
even the left palm is

00:02:13.340 --> 00:02:14.750 align:middle line:90%
different than the right palm.

00:02:14.750 --> 00:02:17.940 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What about
identical twins?

00:02:17.940 --> 00:02:20.668 align:middle line:84%
>>MAHABAL: They're identical
only in last names--

00:02:20.668 --> 00:02:22.210 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Facial
structures and stuff.

00:02:22.210 --> 00:02:24.250 align:middle line:84%
>>MAHABAL: --and
facial structure, yeah.

00:02:24.250 --> 00:02:28.370 align:middle line:84%
But astrologically, they're
as different as the leaves

00:02:28.370 --> 00:02:29.170 align:middle line:90%
on a tree.

00:02:29.170 --> 00:02:32.080 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Vernon, explained
to us what is palmistry.

00:02:32.080 --> 00:02:35.740 align:middle line:84%
>>MAHABAL: Palmistry
is the ability

00:02:35.740 --> 00:02:40.030 align:middle line:84%
to look at our life purpose
through the anciency

00:02:40.030 --> 00:02:41.060 align:middle line:90%
of our hands.

00:02:41.060 --> 00:02:42.490 align:middle line:90%
It's a GPS.

00:02:42.490 --> 00:02:46.150 align:middle line:84%
The soul within the
heart sends its message

00:02:46.150 --> 00:02:50.140 align:middle line:84%
through the agency of the
hands, and that message

00:02:50.140 --> 00:02:51.820 align:middle line:90%
is, what is our life purpose?

00:02:51.820 --> 00:02:53.620 align:middle line:90%
What are we here to accomplish?

00:02:53.620 --> 00:02:55.720 align:middle line:84%
What are our past
life challenges?

00:02:55.720 --> 00:03:00.250 align:middle line:84%
What are we here to
accomplish that makes

00:03:00.250 --> 00:03:02.140 align:middle line:90%
it different than other people?

00:03:02.140 --> 00:03:04.060 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Did it
take you a long time

00:03:04.060 --> 00:03:06.782 align:middle line:90%
to learn how to read palms?

00:03:06.782 --> 00:03:08.240 align:middle line:84%
>>MAHABAL: That's
a great question.

00:03:08.240 --> 00:03:11.830 align:middle line:84%
I studied it extensively,
read every book I could,

00:03:11.830 --> 00:03:16.180 align:middle line:84%
took every lecture I
could, met many palmist

00:03:16.180 --> 00:03:18.260 align:middle line:90%
and studied their systems.

00:03:18.260 --> 00:03:20.560 align:middle line:84%
It did come a little
bit easier to me

00:03:20.560 --> 00:03:23.960 align:middle line:90%
because I think I'm drawn to it.

00:03:23.960 --> 00:03:27.350 align:middle line:84%
But at the same time, I
did work hard to study it.

00:03:27.350 --> 00:03:31.180 align:middle line:84%
But it is something that
I could easily inculcate.

00:03:31.180 --> 00:03:34.400 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: When did you
decide to make it a career?

00:03:34.400 --> 00:03:36.650 align:middle line:84%
>>MAHABAL: When nothing else
worked for me in my life.

00:03:36.650 --> 00:03:39.380 align:middle line:90%


00:03:39.380 --> 00:03:42.200 align:middle line:84%
Though, I would try this,
and I would try that.

00:03:42.200 --> 00:03:44.990 align:middle line:84%
And at the same time, I
always kept my door open

00:03:44.990 --> 00:03:46.280 align:middle line:90%
to look at hands.

00:03:46.280 --> 00:03:50.655 align:middle line:84%
And when I kept my door
open to look at hands,

00:03:50.655 --> 00:03:51.780 align:middle line:90%
everybody would come to me.

00:03:51.780 --> 00:03:55.140 align:middle line:84%
I remember, one time, I was
traveling with a rock and roll

00:03:55.140 --> 00:03:55.940 align:middle line:90%
band.

00:03:55.940 --> 00:03:58.557 align:middle line:84%
I grew up with these people,
and they would sometimes

00:03:58.557 --> 00:04:00.890 align:middle line:84%
have me go on the road with
them and sell their t-shirts

00:04:00.890 --> 00:04:01.820 align:middle line:90%
and be a roadie.

00:04:01.820 --> 00:04:05.750 align:middle line:84%
And at one of their
big Hollywood parties,

00:04:05.750 --> 00:04:08.390 align:middle line:84%
I was reading all these
rock stars' hands.

00:04:08.390 --> 00:04:11.570 align:middle line:90%
This was 1986.

00:04:11.570 --> 00:04:17.630 align:middle line:84%
And I was standing at a
7/11 one day, the next day,

00:04:17.630 --> 00:04:20.390 align:middle line:84%
in the parking lot,
and some guy just

00:04:20.390 --> 00:04:23.750 align:middle line:84%
drives up in a car
into the parking lot,

00:04:23.750 --> 00:04:25.640 align:middle line:84%
gets out of the
car, slams the door,

00:04:25.640 --> 00:04:28.560 align:middle line:84%
and said, what are you hanging
out with these rock and roll

00:04:28.560 --> 00:04:29.360 align:middle line:90%
people for?

00:04:29.360 --> 00:04:33.320 align:middle line:84%
You gave me a great
reading yesterday,

00:04:33.320 --> 00:04:36.050 align:middle line:84%
and that's what you should
be doing as a career.

00:04:36.050 --> 00:04:40.040 align:middle line:84%
He got back in the car, slammed
the door, and just drove away.

00:04:40.040 --> 00:04:42.500 align:middle line:84%
And at that moment, I
said-- that moment, I said,

00:04:42.500 --> 00:04:46.700 align:middle line:84%
in LA and Sepulveda
Boulevard, Venice Boulevard,

00:04:46.700 --> 00:04:48.900 align:middle line:84%
I just said, this is
what I have to do.

00:04:48.900 --> 00:04:49.700 align:middle line:90%
I'm going back to--

00:04:49.700 --> 00:04:52.520 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to go back to New
York and make it my career.

00:04:52.520 --> 00:04:54.560 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Did we know
any of these rock stars

00:04:54.560 --> 00:04:56.600 align:middle line:90%
if you mentioned who they were?

00:04:56.600 --> 00:04:58.430 align:middle line:84%
>>MAHABAL: Yeah, I've
read the hands of--

00:04:58.430 --> 00:05:04.010 align:middle line:84%
that was a tour with Motorhead
and the "Crone" mags.

00:05:04.010 --> 00:05:07.190 align:middle line:84%
And then I've read the hands of
so many rock and roll people--

00:05:07.190 --> 00:05:08.630 align:middle line:90%
Gene Simmons.

00:05:08.630 --> 00:05:09.530 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Lemmy?

00:05:09.530 --> 00:05:10.620 align:middle line:90%
>>MAHABAL: Yeah.

00:05:10.620 --> 00:05:11.420 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:05:11.420 --> 00:05:12.545 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: You knew them all.

00:05:12.545 --> 00:05:16.310 align:middle line:84%
>>MAHABAL: I was lucky to be
able to be in New York and grow

00:05:16.310 --> 00:05:19.670 align:middle line:90%
up with that whole--

00:05:19.670 --> 00:05:24.167 align:middle line:84%
the beginning of the early
metal world, metal music.

00:05:24.167 --> 00:05:26.000 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Never did
Elvis' hands or anything?

00:05:26.000 --> 00:05:27.980 align:middle line:84%
>>MAHABAL: No,
unfortunately, not.

00:05:27.980 --> 00:05:29.870 align:middle line:84%
I wish-- I'd seen
him on the internet.

00:05:29.870 --> 00:05:31.453 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You might
have saved his life

00:05:31.453 --> 00:05:33.560 align:middle line:90%
if you have looked at it.

00:05:33.560 --> 00:05:35.840 align:middle line:84%
When you read
palms, can you tell

00:05:35.840 --> 00:05:37.580 align:middle line:84%
if someone's going
to live a long life

00:05:37.580 --> 00:05:38.840 align:middle line:90%
or anything like that?

00:05:38.840 --> 00:05:40.580 align:middle line:90%
>>MAHABAL: Yes, you can.

00:05:40.580 --> 00:05:43.820 align:middle line:84%
But I think it's
important to not

00:05:43.820 --> 00:05:49.040 align:middle line:84%
tell a person's longevity
unless you can save them

00:05:49.040 --> 00:05:51.830 align:middle line:90%
from some difficult calamity.

00:05:51.830 --> 00:05:55.280 align:middle line:84%
So for instance, if a person
is 30, or 40 or, even 50,

00:05:55.280 --> 00:05:58.580 align:middle line:84%
and they're going there may
be taking too many drugs

00:05:58.580 --> 00:06:01.820 align:middle line:84%
or doing bad
activities, then I'll

00:06:01.820 --> 00:06:06.170 align:middle line:84%
say, hey, get out of this so
that you can live a good life.

00:06:06.170 --> 00:06:07.670 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Get out
of it quickly, too.

00:06:07.670 --> 00:06:08.470 align:middle line:90%
>>MAHABAL: Yeah.

00:06:08.470 --> 00:06:13.370 align:middle line:84%
But I don't ever like to plant
a number in somebody's mind

00:06:13.370 --> 00:06:15.710 align:middle line:84%
because that may
actually happen.

00:06:15.710 --> 00:06:17.480 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Vernon, on
the Gaia program,

00:06:17.480 --> 00:06:20.090 align:middle line:84%
"Open Minds," Ellen Goldberg
talks about the history

00:06:20.090 --> 00:06:21.050 align:middle line:90%
of reading palms.

00:06:21.050 --> 00:06:24.688 align:middle line:84%
I want to get your
reaction to what she says.

00:06:24.688 --> 00:06:26.480 align:middle line:84%
>>ELLEN GOLDBERG: I
think the roots go back

00:06:26.480 --> 00:06:28.490 align:middle line:90%
to the dawn of time.

00:06:28.490 --> 00:06:35.300 align:middle line:10%
When we see the hands on
cave paintings, you know?

00:06:35.300 --> 00:06:38.870 align:middle line:84%
Everywhere from some of
them, from 25,000 years

00:06:38.870 --> 00:06:42.800 align:middle line:84%
before the Christian
era, many from 8,000,

00:06:42.800 --> 00:06:47.540 align:middle line:84%
9,000 years BCE, we
see that people knew

00:06:47.540 --> 00:06:49.070 align:middle line:90%
that the hands were unique.

00:06:49.070 --> 00:06:52.060 align:middle line:90%


00:06:52.060 --> 00:06:54.520 align:middle line:90%
We did not have social media.

00:06:54.520 --> 00:06:57.460 align:middle line:84%
There were no books,
but there were tribes.

00:06:57.460 --> 00:06:58.780 align:middle line:90%
There were stories.

00:06:58.780 --> 00:07:01.570 align:middle line:84%
And as people gathered
together, they

00:07:01.570 --> 00:07:05.770 align:middle line:84%
started to discuss things that
they saw both in the heavens

00:07:05.770 --> 00:07:07.780 align:middle line:90%
and in the hands.

00:07:07.780 --> 00:07:13.390 align:middle line:84%
And so, these were some of the
earliest mystical sciences that

00:07:13.390 --> 00:07:18.190 align:middle line:84%
were developed and really laid
the groundwork for so many

00:07:18.190 --> 00:07:20.290 align:middle line:90%
other things that came later.

00:07:20.290 --> 00:07:24.890 align:middle line:84%
When we look at, say,
palmistry as we know it,

00:07:24.890 --> 00:07:28.540 align:middle line:84%
we know that the Chinese
used fingerprinting

00:07:28.540 --> 00:07:32.592 align:middle line:84%
for identification 1,000 years
before we did in the West.

00:07:32.592 --> 00:07:33.550 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA MEREDITH: Yes.

00:07:33.550 --> 00:07:34.350 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:07:34.350 --> 00:07:37.660 align:middle line:84%
>>GOLDBERG: They used it
for diagnosis, certainly,

00:07:37.660 --> 00:07:41.060 align:middle line:90%
way before that as well.

00:07:41.060 --> 00:07:44.260 align:middle line:84%
Do we really whether it
came its first roots were

00:07:44.260 --> 00:07:46.420 align:middle line:90%
from India or from China?

00:07:46.420 --> 00:07:49.790 align:middle line:84%
I, myself, can't make
a good call on that,

00:07:49.790 --> 00:07:54.730 align:middle line:84%
but I know that we brought
back so much from the Persians.

00:07:54.730 --> 00:07:56.110 align:middle line:90%
>>MEREDITH: Yes.

00:07:56.110 --> 00:07:58.780 align:middle line:84%
>>GOLDBERG: They also had
exquisite astrology, right?

00:07:58.780 --> 00:08:03.970 align:middle line:84%
All of these great nations,
all of these great areas

00:08:03.970 --> 00:08:09.940 align:middle line:84%
of the world had both astrology
and palmistry traditions

00:08:09.940 --> 00:08:12.410 align:middle line:84%
reaching back
thousands of years.

00:08:12.410 --> 00:08:15.250 align:middle line:84%
One of the things that
I get a big kick out of

00:08:15.250 --> 00:08:20.680 align:middle line:84%
is that, in the Vedas, these
ancient scriptures from India,

00:08:20.680 --> 00:08:25.900 align:middle line:84%
about 2000 BC, there is actually
an admonition to the monks,

00:08:25.900 --> 00:08:28.210 align:middle line:84%
saying, you know,
it's really not

00:08:28.210 --> 00:08:30.980 align:middle line:90%
right to read palms for money.

00:08:30.980 --> 00:08:32.869 align:middle line:90%
And so, therefore, we know--

00:08:32.869 --> 00:08:33.669 align:middle line:90%
>>MEREDITH: Yes.

00:08:33.669 --> 00:08:37.190 align:middle line:84%
>>GOLDBERG: --it was already
a profession 2000 BC.

00:08:37.190 --> 00:08:37.990 align:middle line:90%
>>MEREDITH: Yes.

00:08:37.990 --> 00:08:39.900 align:middle line:84%
>>GOLDBERG: You could do
it, but not for money--

00:08:39.900 --> 00:08:40.210 align:middle line:90%
>>MEREDITH: For money.

00:08:40.210 --> 00:08:40.870 align:middle line:90%
>>GOLDBERG: --for a monk.

00:08:40.870 --> 00:08:43.210 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Vernon, how did
Ellen do explaining palmistry?

00:08:43.210 --> 00:08:46.630 align:middle line:84%
>>MAHABAL: I completely agree
with everything that she said.

00:08:46.630 --> 00:08:52.840 align:middle line:84%
In fact, the earliest known
book on palmistry in Sanskrit,

00:08:52.840 --> 00:08:55.225 align:middle line:84%
it's called the
"Hasta-samudrika-sastra."

00:08:55.225 --> 00:08:57.580 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: How old is that book?

00:08:57.580 --> 00:09:00.970 align:middle line:84%
>>MAHABAL: It was
written in 3102 BC

00:09:00.970 --> 00:09:02.672 align:middle line:90%
by a person named Garga Acharya.

00:09:02.672 --> 00:09:03.880 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: 5,000-year-old book.

00:09:03.880 --> 00:09:05.110 align:middle line:90%
>>MAHABAL: 5,000 year old.

00:09:05.110 --> 00:09:07.300 align:middle line:84%
It's as old as the
"Bhagavad Gita."

00:09:07.300 --> 00:09:10.360 align:middle line:84%
And that's the old--
that's when, let's say,

00:09:10.360 --> 00:09:16.000 align:middle line:84%
writing started in
that Vedic culture.

00:09:16.000 --> 00:09:19.870 align:middle line:84%
So in the Vedic
civilization, they

00:09:19.870 --> 00:09:22.630 align:middle line:84%
will say that
palmistry and astrology

00:09:22.630 --> 00:09:25.720 align:middle line:84%
have been around as long
as human beings have

00:09:25.720 --> 00:09:27.040 align:middle line:90%
been on this planet.

00:09:27.040 --> 00:09:29.780 align:middle line:84%
And humans beings have
been on this planet,

00:09:29.780 --> 00:09:33.610 align:middle line:84%
according to the Vedic version,
for millions of years--

00:09:33.610 --> 00:09:35.260 align:middle line:90%
millions of years.

00:09:35.260 --> 00:09:43.720 align:middle line:84%
And it is part of a spiritual
or religious tradition

00:09:43.720 --> 00:09:47.770 align:middle line:84%
to read the hands and look
at the astrological chart

00:09:47.770 --> 00:09:49.090 align:middle line:90%
of people.

00:09:49.090 --> 00:09:52.360 align:middle line:84%
It goes hand-in-hand with
understanding a person's life

00:09:52.360 --> 00:09:54.610 align:middle line:90%
destiny and Dharma.

00:09:54.610 --> 00:09:58.120 align:middle line:84%
In fact, what's interesting,
in the Vedic view,

00:09:58.120 --> 00:10:00.640 align:middle line:84%
it was the astrologer
or the promised

00:10:00.640 --> 00:10:06.220 align:middle line:84%
who gave the name to the
child, not the parents.

00:10:06.220 --> 00:10:07.660 align:middle line:90%
In ancient Vedic culture--

00:10:07.660 --> 00:10:09.895 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: The palm reader
gave the name of the child

00:10:09.895 --> 00:10:10.150 align:middle line:90%
to the parents.

00:10:10.150 --> 00:10:12.800 align:middle line:84%
>>MAHABAL: Yes, according to
what they saw astrologically.

00:10:12.800 --> 00:10:14.200 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You're going to
be William or whatever.

00:10:14.200 --> 00:10:14.740 align:middle line:90%
>>MAHABAL: Yeah.

00:10:14.740 --> 00:10:16.660 align:middle line:84%
According to what they
saw astrologically

00:10:16.660 --> 00:10:19.540 align:middle line:84%
in the hand or the chart,
they would give the child

00:10:19.540 --> 00:10:23.620 align:middle line:84%
a name based on the
vibrations of the planet

00:10:23.620 --> 00:10:26.800 align:middle line:84%
so that they would be in harmony
with the planetary forces.

00:10:26.800 --> 00:10:31.060 align:middle line:84%
And it's interesting what
she says about the idea

00:10:31.060 --> 00:10:35.170 align:middle line:84%
that people did not
do it as a profession.

00:10:35.170 --> 00:10:37.810 align:middle line:84%
They did it as a profession,
but they didn't ask for money.

00:10:37.810 --> 00:10:40.900 align:middle line:84%
It was part of what we call
the Brahmanical culture.

00:10:40.900 --> 00:10:45.640 align:middle line:84%
And the Brahmins were either
doctors, or medicinalists,

00:10:45.640 --> 00:10:47.020 align:middle line:90%
or they were astrologers.

00:10:47.020 --> 00:10:49.750 align:middle line:84%
And they would go to people's
houses and give readings.

00:10:49.750 --> 00:10:53.200 align:middle line:84%
And then, people would give
them donations, or alms,

00:10:53.200 --> 00:10:56.800 align:middle line:84%
or take care of them, give
them milk, give them food.

00:10:56.800 --> 00:10:58.360 align:middle line:84%
And they would go
to the next house.

00:10:58.360 --> 00:11:02.080 align:middle line:84%
So it wasn't that something
that they charged.

00:11:02.080 --> 00:11:06.660 align:middle line:84%
They were considered an
integral part of the kingdom.

00:11:06.660 --> 00:11:07.660 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: And the family.

00:11:07.660 --> 00:11:09.310 align:middle line:90%
>>MAHABAL: And the family, yes.

00:11:09.310 --> 00:11:13.960 align:middle line:84%
So as soon as a child was born,
an astrologer or a palmist

00:11:13.960 --> 00:11:17.350 align:middle line:84%
was called to ascertain
the life destiny

00:11:17.350 --> 00:11:20.950 align:middle line:84%
of the child and, of course,
how the parents can better

00:11:20.950 --> 00:11:21.970 align:middle line:90%
raise that child.

00:11:21.970 --> 00:11:24.730 align:middle line:84%
They told the
parents, for instance,

00:11:24.730 --> 00:11:26.740 align:middle line:84%
what this person's
emotions are going

00:11:26.740 --> 00:11:28.240 align:middle line:84%
to be like, what
the challenges are,

00:11:28.240 --> 00:11:32.440 align:middle line:84%
what the good news is, what they
should be getting involved in,

00:11:32.440 --> 00:11:34.660 align:middle line:84%
what the relationship they
had in the previous life

00:11:34.660 --> 00:11:35.720 align:middle line:90%
with that child.

00:11:35.720 --> 00:11:42.160 align:middle line:84%
So the palmist and
astrologer were a valued part

00:11:42.160 --> 00:11:44.560 align:middle line:90%
of the ancient Vedic culture.

00:11:44.560 --> 00:11:48.340 align:middle line:84%
And the ancient Vedic culture
goes back millions of years,

00:11:48.340 --> 00:11:52.520 align:middle line:84%
according to a book called
"Srimad Bhagavad Gita."

00:11:52.520 --> 00:11:55.730 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Can you imagine
the first palm reader ever,

00:11:55.730 --> 00:12:01.092 align:middle line:84%
looking at a hand, coming
up with all kinds of things?

00:12:01.092 --> 00:12:02.550 align:middle line:84%
>>MAHABAL: It's
absolutely amazing.

00:12:02.550 --> 00:12:09.600 align:middle line:84%
In fact, the Vedas say that it
was demigods and goddesses who

00:12:09.600 --> 00:12:13.530 align:middle line:84%
taught this astrological
science to mankind.

00:12:13.530 --> 00:12:17.550 align:middle line:84%
In fact, the book,
"Hasta-samudrika-sastra,"

00:12:17.550 --> 00:12:23.430 align:middle line:84%
hasta means hand, and samudrika
means the divine study of it,

00:12:23.430 --> 00:12:25.680 align:middle line:90%
and sastra means scripture.

00:12:25.680 --> 00:12:29.880 align:middle line:84%
So literally, this book
that was written by Garga

00:12:29.880 --> 00:12:35.280 align:middle line:84%
means the divine
understanding of human destiny

00:12:35.280 --> 00:12:37.260 align:middle line:90%
according to the stars.

00:12:37.260 --> 00:12:39.720 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: If you never met
somebody, Vernon, and you

00:12:39.720 --> 00:12:41.880 align:middle line:84%
looked at their
palm, would you be

00:12:41.880 --> 00:12:45.780 align:middle line:84%
able to ascertain their
personality, their character

00:12:45.780 --> 00:12:47.340 align:middle line:90%
from just reading a palm?

00:12:47.340 --> 00:12:50.250 align:middle line:84%
>>MAHABAL: Yes, you can, and
that's the beauty of astrology.

00:12:50.250 --> 00:12:52.050 align:middle line:90%
That's the beauty of palmistry.

00:12:52.050 --> 00:12:58.620 align:middle line:84%
The hand is the visible
part of the brain.

00:12:58.620 --> 00:13:04.740 align:middle line:84%
It is that part of ourselves
that we cannot read,

00:13:04.740 --> 00:13:06.870 align:middle line:84%
but it comes to us
through our hand.

00:13:06.870 --> 00:13:08.220 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Is it our personality?

00:13:08.220 --> 00:13:09.840 align:middle line:84%
>>MAHABAL: It is
our personality.

00:13:09.840 --> 00:13:11.260 align:middle line:90%
It's our consciousness.

00:13:11.260 --> 00:13:13.800 align:middle line:84%
It's what we bring
from previous lives.

00:13:13.800 --> 00:13:16.920 align:middle line:84%
In fact, that's the beauty
of reading for someone

00:13:16.920 --> 00:13:19.860 align:middle line:90%
who's a young child.

00:13:19.860 --> 00:13:23.940 align:middle line:84%
And that just as we look at
a tree, we see an above--

00:13:23.940 --> 00:13:28.470 align:middle line:84%
we see a tree may be so
many hundreds of feet,

00:13:28.470 --> 00:13:36.190 align:middle line:84%
but on the ground, that tree may
be seven or eight times bigger.

00:13:36.190 --> 00:13:39.600 align:middle line:84%
And that's like the idea
of the previous lives.

00:13:39.600 --> 00:13:43.890 align:middle line:84%
So on your hands, we can see
a person's previous lives

00:13:43.890 --> 00:13:46.560 align:middle line:84%
and then understand how they're
going to act in this life.

00:13:46.560 --> 00:13:51.570 align:middle line:84%
So that part, the idea of
a person's previous lives,

00:13:51.570 --> 00:13:53.290 align:middle line:90%
we can't see that.

00:13:53.290 --> 00:13:54.840 align:middle line:84%
The person doesn't
understand that.

00:13:54.840 --> 00:13:58.920 align:middle line:84%
But by our hands, we can see
what a person went through,

00:13:58.920 --> 00:14:01.727 align:middle line:84%
where they were, what they
did, what their challenges are.

00:14:01.727 --> 00:14:03.060 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Their ups, their downs.

00:14:03.060 --> 00:14:05.250 align:middle line:84%
>>MAHABAL: Their
ups and their downs.

00:14:05.250 --> 00:14:10.140 align:middle line:84%
People sometimes say, George,
that life doesn't come

00:14:10.140 --> 00:14:12.750 align:middle line:90%
with instructions, but it does.

00:14:12.750 --> 00:14:14.523 align:middle line:90%
It's on our hands.

00:14:14.523 --> 00:14:15.690 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's fascinating.

00:14:15.690 --> 00:14:16.020 align:middle line:90%
>>MAHABAL: Yeah.

00:14:16.020 --> 00:14:17.280 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It truly is.

00:14:17.280 --> 00:14:20.520 align:middle line:90%
How does this tie into karma?

00:14:20.520 --> 00:14:23.550 align:middle line:84%
>>MAHABAL: There's
three types of karma.

00:14:23.550 --> 00:14:26.280 align:middle line:84%
Karma simply means
action and reaction.

00:14:26.280 --> 00:14:28.050 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Or what goes
around comes around.

00:14:28.050 --> 00:14:29.160 align:middle line:84%
>>MAHABAL: What goes
around comes around.

00:14:29.160 --> 00:14:30.240 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:14:30.240 --> 00:14:34.590 align:middle line:84%
For instance, we
reap what we sow.

00:14:34.590 --> 00:14:35.775 align:middle line:90%
And it's very obvious.

00:14:35.775 --> 00:14:36.900 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: I agree with that.

00:14:36.900 --> 00:14:38.340 align:middle line:90%
>>MAHABAL: We see that.

00:14:38.340 --> 00:14:40.410 align:middle line:90%
It's so obvious in palmistry.

00:14:40.410 --> 00:14:42.540 align:middle line:84%
For instance, people
ask me a lot--

00:14:42.540 --> 00:14:43.800 align:middle line:90%
am I going to win the lottery?

00:14:43.800 --> 00:14:46.350 align:middle line:84%
It's a common thing I hear at
a party or something like that.

00:14:46.350 --> 00:14:48.510 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Now, will you know
that through your palm reading?

00:14:48.510 --> 00:14:49.350 align:middle line:90%
>>MAHABAL: Yes, you will.

00:14:49.350 --> 00:14:50.160 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Really?

00:14:50.160 --> 00:14:52.830 align:middle line:84%
>>MAHABAL: Yeah, and
the interesting thing

00:14:52.830 --> 00:14:56.490 align:middle line:84%
is that if a person wins
the lottery, it means,

00:14:56.490 --> 00:15:00.750 align:middle line:84%
in a previous life, that
person was very pious,

00:15:00.750 --> 00:15:02.460 align:middle line:90%
and they gave to the community.

00:15:02.460 --> 00:15:03.630 align:middle line:90%
They planted trees.

00:15:03.630 --> 00:15:06.690 align:middle line:84%
They opened up a hospital,
maybe they started an orphanage.

00:15:06.690 --> 00:15:10.150 align:middle line:84%
They were just very, very
giving and very generous.

00:15:10.150 --> 00:15:12.600 align:middle line:84%
And then, the next
life, the state

00:15:12.600 --> 00:15:14.342 align:middle line:84%
gives it back to
them, so to speak.

00:15:14.342 --> 00:15:15.300 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It comes back.

00:15:15.300 --> 00:15:19.110 align:middle line:84%
And in the same way,
if we do bad activities

00:15:19.110 --> 00:15:22.620 align:middle line:84%
to ourselves or other
people, it comes back to us,

00:15:22.620 --> 00:15:25.320 align:middle line:84%
and we have to taste the
results of those actions.

00:15:25.320 --> 00:15:27.150 align:middle line:90%
And that's called karma.

00:15:27.150 --> 00:15:31.260 align:middle line:84%
And karma is simply
for purification.

00:15:31.260 --> 00:15:35.550 align:middle line:84%
So a palmist or an astrologer,
especially a Vedically trained

00:15:35.550 --> 00:15:40.080 align:middle line:84%
astrologer or palmist, will say
that suffering is actually not

00:15:40.080 --> 00:15:45.645 align:middle line:84%
for a bad purpose, but it's
simply for our purification

00:15:45.645 --> 00:15:46.770 align:middle line:90%
to make us a better person.

00:15:46.770 --> 00:15:48.312 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: For our
incredible audience,

00:15:48.312 --> 00:15:49.290 align:middle line:90%
would you read my palm?

00:15:49.290 --> 00:15:50.415 align:middle line:90%
>>MAHABAL: I would love to.

00:15:50.415 --> 00:15:51.610 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: How do we start?

00:15:51.610 --> 00:15:53.460 align:middle line:84%
>>MAHABAL: Well, I'll
come sit next to you.

00:15:53.460 --> 00:15:56.630 align:middle line:90%


00:15:56.630 --> 00:16:03.250 align:middle line:84%
So if we look at George's hand,
we see that the palm is square.

00:16:03.250 --> 00:16:04.330 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Is that unusual?

00:16:04.330 --> 00:16:05.200 align:middle line:90%
>>MAHABAL: No.

00:16:05.200 --> 00:16:07.030 align:middle line:84%
We see that the palm
is square, and then we

00:16:07.030 --> 00:16:11.430 align:middle line:84%
see the fingers a little
shorter than the palm.

00:16:11.430 --> 00:16:13.740 align:middle line:84%
So George has what we
call an earth hand.

00:16:13.740 --> 00:16:16.750 align:middle line:84%
There's four basic
shapes of hands.

00:16:16.750 --> 00:16:19.020 align:middle line:84%
One is earth, water,
fire, and air.

00:16:19.020 --> 00:16:22.500 align:middle line:90%
George has a perfect earth hand.

00:16:22.500 --> 00:16:25.020 align:middle line:84%
And what the earth
hand means is that he's

00:16:25.020 --> 00:16:27.990 align:middle line:84%
able to take the ideas
that are within here

00:16:27.990 --> 00:16:31.740 align:middle line:90%
and then make them tangible.

00:16:31.740 --> 00:16:33.960 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I can put our
ideas and make them work?

00:16:33.960 --> 00:16:35.430 align:middle line:90%
>>MAHABAL: Make them work.

00:16:35.430 --> 00:16:38.130 align:middle line:90%
You're a manifester.

00:16:38.130 --> 00:16:42.690 align:middle line:84%
And so, the earth hand
is about establishing

00:16:42.690 --> 00:16:45.970 align:middle line:84%
security and stability on a
subconscious point of view.

00:16:45.970 --> 00:16:47.700 align:middle line:84%
And on a more conscious
point of view,

00:16:47.700 --> 00:16:51.420 align:middle line:84%
the earth hand is about
being able to make your ideas

00:16:51.420 --> 00:16:53.040 align:middle line:90%
tangible and practical.

00:16:53.040 --> 00:16:56.970 align:middle line:84%
And George, you have
a textbook earth hand.

00:16:56.970 --> 00:17:00.360 align:middle line:84%
Just like earth itself is very
grounded and very practical,

00:17:00.360 --> 00:17:01.800 align:middle line:90%
you are very practical.

00:17:01.800 --> 00:17:04.901 align:middle line:84%
Yet, your lines here show
that you're a visionary.

00:17:04.901 --> 00:17:06.359 align:middle line:84%
You're into the
metaphysical world.

00:17:06.359 --> 00:17:08.400 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I assume I was
born this way, right?

00:17:08.400 --> 00:17:09.810 align:middle line:90%
I didn't change over time.

00:17:09.810 --> 00:17:11.880 align:middle line:84%
>>MAHABAL: No, the hand's
shape stays the same.

00:17:11.880 --> 00:17:16.380 align:middle line:84%
The hand shape is actually
how you approach life.

00:17:16.380 --> 00:17:18.750 align:middle line:90%
It's like the car that we drive.

00:17:18.750 --> 00:17:22.060 align:middle line:84%
So the way you approach
life is in a very practical,

00:17:22.060 --> 00:17:26.130 align:middle line:84%
down to Earth way, and
that's the earth hand.

00:17:26.130 --> 00:17:29.550 align:middle line:84%
And your thumb is
about 45 degrees angle.

00:17:29.550 --> 00:17:31.800 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes, the thumb
could be out here.

00:17:31.800 --> 00:17:34.110 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes, it could be
actually closer to the hand.

00:17:34.110 --> 00:17:37.210 align:middle line:84%
When the thumb is at a
45-degree angle like this,

00:17:37.210 --> 00:17:43.380 align:middle line:84%
it means that you have a very
strong sense of confidence

00:17:43.380 --> 00:17:45.120 align:middle line:90%
and self-awareness.

00:17:45.120 --> 00:17:51.260 align:middle line:84%
But at the same time, you can
yield to other people's needs

00:17:51.260 --> 00:17:53.210 align:middle line:90%
or wants.

00:17:53.210 --> 00:17:55.460 align:middle line:84%
When the thumb is
way out here, it

00:17:55.460 --> 00:17:57.870 align:middle line:84%
shows a tremendous
amount of confidence,

00:17:57.870 --> 00:18:01.340 align:middle line:84%
sometimes overactive
confidence, maybe even ego.

00:18:01.340 --> 00:18:06.770 align:middle line:84%
When it's here, it shows
insecurity and self-doubt.

00:18:06.770 --> 00:18:11.137 align:middle line:84%
When you see people who have a
lot of insecurity or self-doubt

00:18:11.137 --> 00:18:13.470 align:middle line:84%
and lack of confidence, it
stays very close to the hand.

00:18:13.470 --> 00:18:13.790 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Really?

00:18:13.790 --> 00:18:14.590 align:middle line:90%
>>MAHABAL: Yeah.

00:18:14.590 --> 00:18:16.730 align:middle line:90%
But yours is at a--

00:18:16.730 --> 00:18:17.793 align:middle line:90%
yours is at the edge.

00:18:17.793 --> 00:18:19.460 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, it's
naturally like that.

00:18:19.460 --> 00:18:20.600 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Wonderful.

00:18:20.600 --> 00:18:22.970 align:middle line:84%
This is a textbook
example of someone

00:18:22.970 --> 00:18:25.760 align:middle line:84%
who is very
confident, self-aware,

00:18:25.760 --> 00:18:29.090 align:middle line:84%
and at the same time,
very humble and giving

00:18:29.090 --> 00:18:33.170 align:middle line:84%
to other people and being
able to yield when needed.

00:18:33.170 --> 00:18:36.560 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: So if you didn't know
me, and you looked at my hand,

00:18:36.560 --> 00:18:38.600 align:middle line:90%
you would say these same things?

00:18:38.600 --> 00:18:40.640 align:middle line:90%
>>MAHABAL: I would, definitely.

00:18:40.640 --> 00:18:43.280 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I know, when you're on
Coast to Coast, our radio show,

00:18:43.280 --> 00:18:46.700 align:middle line:84%
you'll ask people to look
at their hands-- callers--

00:18:46.700 --> 00:18:49.520 align:middle line:84%
and you'll talk about
the segments of a finger.

00:18:49.520 --> 00:18:50.870 align:middle line:90%
Why are they important?

00:18:50.870 --> 00:18:53.360 align:middle line:84%
>>MAHABAL: Oh, well,
these segments,

00:18:53.360 --> 00:18:58.380 align:middle line:84%
we have 12 all together, and
they are what the astrologers

00:18:58.380 --> 00:18:59.180 align:middle line:90%
call--

00:18:59.180 --> 00:19:00.680 align:middle line:90%
well, we call them the signs.

00:19:00.680 --> 00:19:04.590 align:middle line:84%
So Aries, Taurus, Gemini,
Cancer, Leo, Virgo, like that.

00:19:04.590 --> 00:19:09.170 align:middle line:90%
So all the signs are here.

00:19:09.170 --> 00:19:13.280 align:middle line:84%
The planets are here, and
the houses, the first house,

00:19:13.280 --> 00:19:15.230 align:middle line:84%
second house, third
house are here.

00:19:15.230 --> 00:19:17.570 align:middle line:84%
So this is your
astrological chart.

00:19:17.570 --> 00:19:20.390 align:middle line:84%
In the same way that
an astrologer will

00:19:20.390 --> 00:19:22.910 align:middle line:84%
look at a computer
and see the chart,

00:19:22.910 --> 00:19:25.550 align:middle line:84%
a palmist sees all the
planets, all the signs,

00:19:25.550 --> 00:19:28.050 align:middle line:90%
all the houses in the palm.

00:19:28.050 --> 00:19:30.270 align:middle line:84%
So this is our
astrological chart.

00:19:30.270 --> 00:19:32.710 align:middle line:84%
It's not different from
an astrological chart.

00:19:32.710 --> 00:19:34.950 align:middle line:84%
We can see the same things
that an astrologer can.

00:19:34.950 --> 00:19:38.585 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: So overall, what
would you say about me?

00:19:38.585 --> 00:19:40.210 align:middle line:84%
>>MAHABAL: We're
talking about segment,

00:19:40.210 --> 00:19:42.330 align:middle line:84%
so this is your
strongest segment.

00:19:42.330 --> 00:19:44.880 align:middle line:84%
You see how it's
wider and thicker?

00:19:44.880 --> 00:19:47.520 align:middle line:84%
If I was going to--
if this was a tree,

00:19:47.520 --> 00:19:50.160 align:middle line:84%
you see how this tree is
very, very strong, especially

00:19:50.160 --> 00:19:52.750 align:middle line:90%
the base, much more than this.

00:19:52.750 --> 00:19:55.740 align:middle line:84%
So what this particular
segment shows

00:19:55.740 --> 00:20:01.050 align:middle line:84%
is that you're able to give
people advice and counsel,

