And when he stopped
laughing, he said,

00:29:18.300 --> 00:29:20.430 align:middle line:84%
you know you're in
the right relationship

00:29:20.430 --> 00:29:24.900 align:middle line:84%
when it starts off as a dream
come true and eventually

00:29:24.900 --> 00:29:27.450 align:middle line:84%
devolves into your
worst nightmare.

00:29:27.450 --> 00:29:31.730 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Vernon, have you read
a couple's palms together?

00:29:31.730 --> 00:29:36.830 align:middle line:84%
>>MAHABAL: Many times, and it's
called relationship counseling.

00:29:36.830 --> 00:29:39.560 align:middle line:84%
But yes, many couples have
come to me over the years.

00:29:39.560 --> 00:29:42.740 align:middle line:84%
And one of the most
interesting things

00:29:42.740 --> 00:29:47.810 align:middle line:84%
is that what I see is that
in order for a relationship

00:29:47.810 --> 00:29:51.080 align:middle line:84%
to become successful,
both people

00:29:51.080 --> 00:29:55.430 align:middle line:84%
have to understand the
other person's thinking.

00:29:55.430 --> 00:29:59.210 align:middle line:84%
And this is what I find
to be the difficulty.

00:29:59.210 --> 00:30:01.880 align:middle line:84%
In other words, we tend
to give in relationships

00:30:01.880 --> 00:30:05.510 align:middle line:90%
what we ourselves want or need.

00:30:05.510 --> 00:30:09.260 align:middle line:84%
And what the hand
shows is that--

00:30:09.260 --> 00:30:11.900 align:middle line:84%
and what I try to do
is explain to someone,

00:30:11.900 --> 00:30:13.580 align:middle line:90%
OK, this is the way she is.

00:30:13.580 --> 00:30:14.540 align:middle line:90%
This is her wants.

00:30:14.540 --> 00:30:16.130 align:middle line:90%
This is her needs.

00:30:16.130 --> 00:30:18.680 align:middle line:84%
Think about her
needs, her wants,

00:30:18.680 --> 00:30:23.690 align:middle line:84%
or his needs, and
not put your ideas

00:30:23.690 --> 00:30:24.930 align:middle line:90%
of what you want in there.

00:30:24.930 --> 00:30:27.530 align:middle line:84%
In other words
relationship counseling

00:30:27.530 --> 00:30:30.920 align:middle line:84%
is simply about letting
both parties understand

00:30:30.920 --> 00:30:34.400 align:middle line:84%
how the other person thinks,
and then relationships

00:30:34.400 --> 00:30:36.170 align:middle line:90%
go really smoothly.

00:30:36.170 --> 00:30:39.560 align:middle line:84%
The interesting thing about what
your video was talking about--

00:30:39.560 --> 00:30:41.310 align:middle line:90%
and I agree with them.

00:30:41.310 --> 00:30:44.870 align:middle line:84%
Have you ever seen
people, for instance,

00:30:44.870 --> 00:30:48.510 align:middle line:84%
two people will go dating
for about a month or two,

00:30:48.510 --> 00:30:50.180 align:middle line:84%
and they'll lock
each other's horns

00:30:50.180 --> 00:30:52.158 align:middle line:84%
and start fighting, and
then forget about it.

00:30:52.158 --> 00:30:53.450 align:middle line:90%
They're no longer relationship.

00:30:53.450 --> 00:30:54.658 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It's over, all done.

00:30:54.658 --> 00:30:59.220 align:middle line:84%
>>MAHABAL: And other couples
will have a great time,

00:30:59.220 --> 00:31:01.610 align:middle line:84%
will fight, will lock
horns, will argue,

00:31:01.610 --> 00:31:03.830 align:middle line:90%
but they stay together.

00:31:03.830 --> 00:31:07.160 align:middle line:84%
And that means that those
people have known each other

00:31:07.160 --> 00:31:09.320 align:middle line:84%
in a previous life,
and they're just

00:31:09.320 --> 00:31:11.390 align:middle line:90%
reviving that relationship.

00:31:11.390 --> 00:31:14.030 align:middle line:84%
It's the same for,
let's say, children.

00:31:14.030 --> 00:31:19.400 align:middle line:84%
We can't give-- it's impossible
to give a child so much

00:31:19.400 --> 00:31:24.240 align:middle line:84%
love unless we knew that child
before, or they knew us before.

00:31:24.240 --> 00:31:28.550 align:middle line:84%
So all the loving
relationships in this world,

00:31:28.550 --> 00:31:34.460 align:middle line:84%
we've known them before, whether
they're a child, a parent,

00:31:34.460 --> 00:31:38.330 align:middle line:90%
a relationship, even a dog.

00:31:38.330 --> 00:31:42.020 align:middle line:84%
In the same way
that this life is

00:31:42.020 --> 00:31:44.570 align:middle line:84%
a continuum of the
previous relationship,

00:31:44.570 --> 00:31:48.860 align:middle line:84%
loving relationships simply
continue into the next life.

00:31:48.860 --> 00:31:51.440 align:middle line:84%
And then, when they get through
difficult, they break apart.

00:31:51.440 --> 00:31:55.430 align:middle line:84%
The Vedic view, it gives
an example of, sometimes,

00:31:55.430 --> 00:31:58.010 align:middle line:90%
we see an ocean.

00:31:58.010 --> 00:32:00.170 align:middle line:84%
And on that ocean
could be some straws,

00:32:00.170 --> 00:32:01.520 align:middle line:90%
and they're very far apart.

00:32:01.520 --> 00:32:04.520 align:middle line:84%
Then, a wave brings
two straws together,

00:32:04.520 --> 00:32:07.050 align:middle line:84%
and they stay together
for a long time.

00:32:07.050 --> 00:32:09.500 align:middle line:84%
And then another wave comes
and breaks them apart again,

00:32:09.500 --> 00:32:11.660 align:middle line:84%
and they never see each
other again for a long time

00:32:11.660 --> 00:32:15.140 align:middle line:84%
until, let's say, they go to
the more spiritual planets.

00:32:15.140 --> 00:32:17.720 align:middle line:84%
But that's the way
relationships are.

00:32:17.720 --> 00:32:21.710 align:middle line:84%
We learn a lot about ourselves
through a relationship.

00:32:21.710 --> 00:32:23.930 align:middle line:84%
The person that
we're with learns

00:32:23.930 --> 00:32:25.890 align:middle line:90%
about a lot about themselves.

00:32:25.890 --> 00:32:29.030 align:middle line:84%
And then, when we're done
with that, if you will,

00:32:29.030 --> 00:32:32.330 align:middle line:84%
we go to the next relationship
and learn more, you see.

00:32:32.330 --> 00:32:35.630 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Do we
determine the palm look,

00:32:35.630 --> 00:32:39.710 align:middle line:84%
or does the palm
determine how we act?

00:32:39.710 --> 00:32:42.140 align:middle line:84%
>>MAHABAL: George,
our activities

00:32:42.140 --> 00:32:44.990 align:middle line:90%
determine how the palm looks.

00:32:44.990 --> 00:32:48.290 align:middle line:84%
It's a combination of
both what we have deserve,

00:32:48.290 --> 00:32:50.490 align:middle line:84%
what we deserve,
and what we desire.

00:32:50.490 --> 00:32:53.180 align:middle line:84%
So the activities
of our previous life

00:32:53.180 --> 00:32:55.370 align:middle line:90%
are our karma, so to speak.

00:32:55.370 --> 00:32:58.310 align:middle line:84%
So if we've done good
activities, we get rewarded.

00:32:58.310 --> 00:33:00.830 align:middle line:84%
If a person is very pious
in their previous life,

00:33:00.830 --> 00:33:03.380 align:middle line:84%
they've done things for other
people, they've been generous,

00:33:03.380 --> 00:33:06.200 align:middle line:84%
they've been a good person,
they've been of service,

00:33:06.200 --> 00:33:09.110 align:middle line:84%
in their next life, they
will receive loving parents.

00:33:09.110 --> 00:33:13.430 align:middle line:84%
They'll receive
a nice atmosphere

00:33:13.430 --> 00:33:16.910 align:middle line:84%
to live in, a nice
body, good schooling.

00:33:16.910 --> 00:33:22.100 align:middle line:84%
If a person has done difficult
activities and put people

00:33:22.100 --> 00:33:23.780 align:middle line:84%
into suffering,
then they're going

00:33:23.780 --> 00:33:25.670 align:middle line:84%
to experience that
same suffering.

00:33:25.670 --> 00:33:27.470 align:middle line:84%
They're going to have
to taste that also.

00:33:27.470 --> 00:33:29.570 align:middle line:84%
So again, that's a
purification, too,

00:33:29.570 --> 00:33:31.130 align:middle line:84%
which will make
them in are a better

00:33:31.130 --> 00:33:33.470 align:middle line:90%
person in some next lives.

00:33:33.470 --> 00:33:36.620 align:middle line:84%
But the fact is that
the palm reflects

00:33:36.620 --> 00:33:39.900 align:middle line:84%
what we've done both good
and bad, if you will,

00:33:39.900 --> 00:33:41.690 align:middle line:84%
in the previous
life, and we have

00:33:41.690 --> 00:33:44.240 align:middle line:84%
no control over that
how the palm looks,

00:33:44.240 --> 00:33:46.700 align:middle line:84%
but we have control
over our activities.

00:33:46.700 --> 00:33:49.100 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: If you were to look
at the palm of Elon Musk,

00:33:49.100 --> 00:33:51.980 align:middle line:84%
world's richest
person, Jeff Bezos,

00:33:51.980 --> 00:33:55.670 align:middle line:84%
another multi-billionaire,
would you see similarities there

00:33:55.670 --> 00:33:56.990 align:middle line:90%
between the two of them?

00:33:56.990 --> 00:33:59.150 align:middle line:84%
>>MAHABAL: You'd
be able to see how

00:33:59.150 --> 00:34:01.700 align:middle line:84%
that they're
successful in the world

00:34:01.700 --> 00:34:04.280 align:middle line:84%
or they've got the
spotlight on them.

00:34:04.280 --> 00:34:07.700 align:middle line:84%
You'd be able to
see all the people

00:34:07.700 --> 00:34:08.810 align:middle line:90%
that they have dealt with.

00:34:08.810 --> 00:34:12.300 align:middle line:84%
You'd be able to see that when
they were two years old, part

00:34:12.300 --> 00:34:13.100 align:middle line:90%
of their destiny.

00:34:13.100 --> 00:34:15.980 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Can you predict the
future by looking at a palm?

00:34:15.980 --> 00:34:17.690 align:middle line:84%
>>MAHABAL: Yes,
you absolutely can.

00:34:17.690 --> 00:34:20.179 align:middle line:90%
You absolutely can.

00:34:20.179 --> 00:34:23.960 align:middle line:84%
And even if, at the same
time, we have free will,

00:34:23.960 --> 00:34:28.400 align:middle line:84%
you can also look at
the nature of a person,

00:34:28.400 --> 00:34:30.469 align:middle line:84%
their intelligence,
their psychology,

00:34:30.469 --> 00:34:33.230 align:middle line:84%
their emotional intelligence,
their maturity or lack

00:34:33.230 --> 00:34:35.270 align:middle line:84%
of maturity, and
be able to predict

00:34:35.270 --> 00:34:39.920 align:middle line:84%
what they're going to do or
not going to do over time.

00:34:39.920 --> 00:34:44.469 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: When people come to
you for their palms to be read,

00:34:44.469 --> 00:34:48.190 align:middle line:84%
do you sometimes try to
teach them how to read a palm

00:34:48.190 --> 00:34:49.270 align:middle line:90%
themselves?

00:34:49.270 --> 00:34:54.489 align:middle line:84%
>>MAHABAL: A lot of times,
people, after a reading,

00:34:54.489 --> 00:34:56.830 align:middle line:84%
will start to look
at their own hands

00:34:56.830 --> 00:35:00.880 align:middle line:84%
and maybe buy a book or two
on palmistry after that.

00:35:00.880 --> 00:35:04.510 align:middle line:84%
But usually, people
are not even so much

00:35:04.510 --> 00:35:08.380 align:middle line:84%
aware of all the lines and
configurations on their hands

00:35:08.380 --> 00:35:10.540 align:middle line:84%
until they get a
reading from a palmist.

00:35:10.540 --> 00:35:12.280 align:middle line:84%
And people, at the
end of a reading,

00:35:12.280 --> 00:35:16.720 align:middle line:84%
will say, 90% of the time,
you got all that from my hand?

00:35:16.720 --> 00:35:17.680 align:middle line:90%
I didn't know--

00:35:17.680 --> 00:35:19.840 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know all
that was on my hand.

00:35:19.840 --> 00:35:24.430 align:middle line:84%
So they become fascinated with
the idea that, oh, my God,

00:35:24.430 --> 00:35:25.990 align:middle line:90%
this is my life purpose.

00:35:25.990 --> 00:35:29.840 align:middle line:84%
So then, yes, they
start to buy books on it

00:35:29.840 --> 00:35:31.010 align:middle line:90%
or go to palmistry lectures.

00:35:31.010 --> 00:35:32.210 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: They obsessed with it.

00:35:32.210 --> 00:35:33.252 align:middle line:90%
>>MAHABAL: Yeah, exactly.

00:35:33.252 --> 00:35:35.120 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, other
than when I started

00:35:35.120 --> 00:35:37.070 align:middle line:84%
talking to you about
palms and stuff,

00:35:37.070 --> 00:35:39.890 align:middle line:84%
I didn't realize how many
people are out there that are

00:35:39.890 --> 00:35:41.730 align:middle line:90%
fascinated with this subject.

00:35:41.730 --> 00:35:44.900 align:middle line:84%
We've got a Gaia program
called "Initiation,"

00:35:44.900 --> 00:35:49.160 align:middle line:84%
and Matias De Stefano
talks about hands.

00:35:49.160 --> 00:35:51.620 align:middle line:90%
He loves it.

00:35:51.620 --> 00:35:54.500 align:middle line:10%
>>MATIAS DE STEFANO: If we
go to the first humanity,

00:35:54.500 --> 00:35:57.650 align:middle line:10%
when we were living
in caves, we knew

00:35:57.650 --> 00:36:01.940 align:middle line:10%
that all the patterns that
we have in our existence

00:36:01.940 --> 00:36:08.930 align:middle line:10%
were written in our hands, our
culture, our realities, our way

00:36:08.930 --> 00:36:14.270 align:middle line:10%
of thinking, and the
main five structures

00:36:14.270 --> 00:36:16.280 align:middle line:10%
of the sixth dimension.

00:36:16.280 --> 00:36:22.490 align:middle line:84%
The tetrahedron, the
octahedral cube, icosahedron,

00:36:22.490 --> 00:36:26.610 align:middle line:84%
and dodecahedron are
printed in our five fingers.

00:36:26.610 --> 00:36:32.210 align:middle line:84%
So that's why to remember
the codes, what we used to do

00:36:32.210 --> 00:36:35.990 align:middle line:84%
is to recognize
that our hands were

00:36:35.990 --> 00:36:42.020 align:middle line:84%
the first structure, the first
book to tell all our stories,

00:36:42.020 --> 00:36:43.380 align:middle line:90%
who we really are.

00:36:43.380 --> 00:36:46.550 align:middle line:84%
And that's why hands
were the first books

00:36:46.550 --> 00:36:50.180 align:middle line:84%
to tell the stories
of our origins.

00:36:50.180 --> 00:36:53.960 align:middle line:84%
And from the caves,
we started to do

00:36:53.960 --> 00:36:57.740 align:middle line:84%
the carvings, and the carvings
of the patterns of life.

00:36:57.740 --> 00:37:01.590 align:middle line:84%
Every pattern of life is not
only a circle from the sun,

00:37:01.590 --> 00:37:05.370 align:middle line:84%
but also a spiral that
goes through time.

00:37:05.370 --> 00:37:09.380 align:middle line:84%
So that's why the second
more recognized patterns

00:37:09.380 --> 00:37:13.070 align:middle line:84%
that we can see in all history
of humanity, in every culture,

00:37:13.070 --> 00:37:17.570 align:middle line:84%
is circle within a
circle and a spiral.

00:37:17.570 --> 00:37:21.890 align:middle line:84%
These symbols are all over
the world in every culture,

00:37:21.890 --> 00:37:24.560 align:middle line:84%
and you can find
them everywhere.

00:37:24.560 --> 00:37:28.610 align:middle line:84%
And they all mean the
same, the cycle of life.

00:37:28.610 --> 00:37:31.970 align:middle line:84%
It's like the
Fibonacci spiral that

00:37:31.970 --> 00:37:34.970 align:middle line:84%
helps us understand the
mathematics of the creation

00:37:34.970 --> 00:37:38.450 align:middle line:84%
through the spirals,
through the torus.

00:37:38.450 --> 00:37:40.070 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: When he
held up his hand,

00:37:40.070 --> 00:37:44.420 align:middle line:84%
s you notice that long, long
deep line across his hand?

00:37:44.420 --> 00:37:45.603 align:middle line:90%
>>MAHABAL: Exactly.

00:37:45.603 --> 00:37:46.520 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: What is that?

00:37:46.520 --> 00:37:50.810 align:middle line:84%
>>MAHABAL: OK, so in most
people on the population,

00:37:50.810 --> 00:37:53.100 align:middle line:90%
there's two prominent lines.

00:37:53.100 --> 00:37:57.440 align:middle line:84%
One is called the heart line,
which is closest to the finger.

00:37:57.440 --> 00:38:00.800 align:middle line:84%
And there's a second line
called the headline, which

00:38:00.800 --> 00:38:02.570 align:middle line:90%
is in the middle of the hand.

00:38:02.570 --> 00:38:10.550 align:middle line:84%
Now, what he has is that both
of these lines are one line.

00:38:10.550 --> 00:38:13.700 align:middle line:84%
Palmists sometimes call
that the simian line,

00:38:13.700 --> 00:38:15.230 align:middle line:84%
and I don't like
that terminology.

00:38:15.230 --> 00:38:16.730 align:middle line:90%
I call it the union line.

00:38:16.730 --> 00:38:20.000 align:middle line:84%
It's the union of the
heart and the head.

00:38:20.000 --> 00:38:23.540 align:middle line:84%
So that means, whatever
a person thinks about,

00:38:23.540 --> 00:38:25.340 align:middle line:84%
they put their
intelligence into.

00:38:25.340 --> 00:38:30.020 align:middle line:84%
Whatever a person feels,
whatever a person thinks,

00:38:30.020 --> 00:38:31.130 align:middle line:90%
they put their heart into.

00:38:31.130 --> 00:38:32.360 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: So he's
pretty spiritual?

00:38:32.360 --> 00:38:33.160 align:middle line:90%
>>MAHABAL: Yeah.

00:38:33.160 --> 00:38:37.220 align:middle line:84%
So what that shows is that
when someone has a union line,

00:38:37.220 --> 00:38:40.790 align:middle line:84%
they must do something
that is a passion

00:38:40.790 --> 00:38:42.590 align:middle line:90%
rather than just working a job.

00:38:42.590 --> 00:38:50.800 align:middle line:84%
They must do a career that they
feel a sense of intensity for.

00:38:50.800 --> 00:38:52.750 align:middle line:84%
And they become
intense because it's

00:38:52.750 --> 00:38:55.300 align:middle line:84%
the merging of the
heart and the head.

00:38:55.300 --> 00:38:58.120 align:middle line:84%
So it means that whatever
a person thinks about,

00:38:58.120 --> 00:39:00.100 align:middle line:84%
they become emotionally
involved in.

00:39:00.100 --> 00:39:05.080 align:middle line:84%
And whatever they feel, they put
all of their intelligence into.

00:39:05.080 --> 00:39:09.040 align:middle line:84%
And I like what he was saying
earlier about the book of life.

00:39:09.040 --> 00:39:11.620 align:middle line:84%
Our hands are the
book of our life.

00:39:11.620 --> 00:39:14.420 align:middle line:84%
When I'm looking at a hand,
I'm looking chapter by chapter

00:39:14.420 --> 00:39:15.220 align:middle line:90%
by chapter.

00:39:15.220 --> 00:39:16.750 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: You agree with that?

00:39:16.750 --> 00:39:17.950 align:middle line:90%
>>MAHABAL: 100%.

00:39:17.950 --> 00:39:21.050 align:middle line:84%
Now, the interesting thing,
he's talking about the spiral.

00:39:21.050 --> 00:39:22.690 align:middle line:84%
And I like that
idea because this

00:39:22.690 --> 00:39:25.690 align:middle line:84%
is what the new age, and
the mind, body, spirit world

00:39:25.690 --> 00:39:27.640 align:middle line:90%
has talked a lot about.

00:39:27.640 --> 00:39:30.550 align:middle line:84%
The spiral has to do with
the oneness of things.

00:39:30.550 --> 00:39:32.120 align:middle line:90%
In other words, we're all one.

00:39:32.120 --> 00:39:33.820 align:middle line:90%
We're part and parcel of God.

00:39:33.820 --> 00:39:36.730 align:middle line:84%
In the Vedic view,
they call that Brahman.

00:39:36.730 --> 00:39:40.750 align:middle line:84%
Brahman simply means
the rays of God.

00:39:40.750 --> 00:39:43.720 align:middle line:84%
In other words, we're
part and parcel of God.

00:39:43.720 --> 00:39:46.360 align:middle line:84%
Just like it said in
the "Bhagavad Gita"

00:39:46.360 --> 00:39:49.660 align:middle line:84%
that all the drops
of water of an ocean

00:39:49.660 --> 00:39:54.110 align:middle line:84%
contain everything
that the ocean has it's

00:39:54.110 --> 00:39:55.880 align:middle line:90%
this that they're infinitesimal.

00:39:55.880 --> 00:39:58.070 align:middle line:90%
So in that way, we're one.

00:39:58.070 --> 00:40:01.370 align:middle line:84%
We're one with in
spiritual substance.

00:40:01.370 --> 00:40:04.820 align:middle line:84%
But what an astrologer or
a palmist can talk about

00:40:04.820 --> 00:40:08.520 align:middle line:84%
is that we're simultaneously
one and different.

00:40:08.520 --> 00:40:10.850 align:middle line:84%
